text: Grevillea quinquenervis, also known as the five-nerved grevillea, is a shrub of the genus Grevillea native to a small area on the western end of Kangaroo Island in South Australia. The erect dense shrub typically grows to a height of and has angular and ridged branchlets. It has sublinear to oblong-elliptic or narrowly obovate leaves with a blade that is long and wide. ==See also== * List of Grevillea species ==References== quinquenervis Category:Proteales of Australia Category:Taxa named by John McConnell Black
